               <p>I am an officer; I apprehended the prisoner the 19th of February, in <placeName id="t17900224-75-crimeloc420">Shoreditch</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17900224-75-crimeloc420" type="placeName" value="Shoreditch"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17900224-75-crimeloc420" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17900224-75-off418 t17900224-75-crimeloc420"></join> parish, in a house; in the same house where I took her before; I was present when she was convicted; I gave evidence; I had an information of her.</p>
               <p>(The Record of January 1784, read by 
               <persName id="t17900224-75-person728">
                  Thomas
                   Shelton
               <interp inst="t17900224-75-person728" type="surname" value="Shelton"></interp>
